      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 381: Each failure increments `info.failures` without an upper bound. A long-running daemon repeatedly failing to reconnect the same peer can eventually overflow the unsigned counter, resetting the backoff calculation and re-enabling eager reconnect behavior. Clamp the counter once it reaches the threshold/cap.\n```suggestion\n        if (info.failures \u003c RECONNECT_ONDEMAND_THRESHOLD + 1)\n            info.failures++;\n```",
