      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 396: The async timer handler does not verify that the fired wait still corresponds to the current retry generation. If a timer expiry races with `markConnected()` cancelling the timer, a stale successful handler can still run and proactively reconnect a node that is already connected or whose retry was superseded. Capture the expected retry time/generation and re-check state under the mutex before connecting.\n```suggestion\n    auto retryAt \u003d info.nextRetry;\n    info.timer-\u003easync_wait([w \u003d weak(), nodeId, retryAt](const asio::error_code\u0026 ec) {\n        if (ec)\n            return;\n        if (auto shared \u003d w.lock()) {\n            std::lock_guard lock(shared-\u003emutex);\n            auto it \u003d shared-\u003ereconnectInfos_.find(nodeId);\n            if (it \u003d\u003d shared-\u003ereconnectInfos_.end() || it-\u003esecond.nextRetry !\u003d retryAt || shared-\u003eisConnectedWith(nodeId))\n                return;\n            // unlock before tryConnect in the final implementation\n        }\n    });\n```",
      "revId": "157a63aa76b20739bc0a7654d4cae6d59f087df4",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
