      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 397: The reconnect timer only calls maintainBuckets({nodeId}), but maintainBuckets does not actually attempt the explicit node if the bucket is already full. Because `nodes` starts with `toConnect` but bucket iteration may skip/ignore the node\u0027s bucket when full, the delayed reconnect may be lost or delayed indefinitely until unrelated maintenance happens. A scheduled retry should attempt the target node directly after the timer fires, while still allowing normal bucket maintenance separately.\n```suggestion\n        if (auto shared \u003d w.lock())\n            shared-\u003etryConnect(nodeId);\n```",
